cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SD (Sound), as it deals with the problem of singing voice separation in audio recordings. It could also belong to cs.SI (Speech and Natural Language Processing) as it involves separating the vocal part from mixed music audio recordings. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses deep learning techniques, and cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.MM (Multimedia) as it deals with audio signal processing.
